description.narrative: The 2021/22 UNICEF Eswatini workplans continued to be one of the exemplary workplans in the region (ESAR). Monitoring of program implementation on monthly, quarterly, mid and end of year contributed to an;over 80% achievement of planned results. Four of the planned surveys were completed in 2021 and have provided information for improving programming in the areas of nutrition, public finance management, ECD and in community health. Furthermore, MICS implementation achieved a critical milestone of data collection in 2021 and the report will be available in 2022.; | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:11/01/2022
